    • Method Detail

      • crossover

        public static <E> Product2<java.lang.Iterable<E>,java.lang.Iterable<E>> crossover(java.lang.Iterable<E> x,
                                                                                  java.lang.Iterable<E> y,
                                                                                  java.util.Set<java.lang.Integer> indices)
        Create a crossover product between two Iterables with crossovers at given indices. This means that both Iterables in the returned product are a combination of the input iterables in such a way, that the constructed iterable switches the input iterable at each given position. Both input Iterables will be zipped with Products.zip(Iterable, Iterable). Therefore the returned Iterables will have the same size equal to the size of the input iterable with the fewest elements.
        Type Parameters:
        E - the type of the elements in Iterables
        Parameters:
        x - The first Iterable
        y - The second Iterable
        indices - the indices at which to do the crossovers
        Returns:
        a product of Iterables with crossovers at the given indices

                                  java.util.List<?> second)
        Computes the hamming distance between the two lists first and second which must be of equal length.
        Parameters:

        second - the second list
        Returns:
        the number of positions where the elements in both lists are not equal
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - is the lists are not of the same length
